.TH "of_phy_get_and_connect" 9 "of_phy_get_and_connect" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
of_phy_get_and_connect \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct phy_device *" of_phy_get_and_connect
.BI "(struct net_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct device_node *np "  ","
.BI "void (*hndlr)(struct net_device *) "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
pointer to net_device claiming the phy
.IP "np" 12
Pointer to device tree node for the net_device claiming the phy
.IP "hndlr" 12
Link state callback for the network device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
- Get phy node and connect to the phy described in the device tree
If successful, returns a pointer to the phy_device with the embedded
struct device refcount incremented by one, or NULL on failure. The
refcount must be dropped by calling \fBphy_disconnect\fP or \fBphy_detach\fP.
